5|$|In the Earth's crust, bismuth {{is about}} twice as {{abundant}} as gold. The most important ores of bismuth are bismuthinite and <b>bismite.</b> Native bismuth is known from Australia, Bolivia, and China.|$|E
50|$|<b>Bismite</b> is a {{secondary}} oxidation zone mineral which forms from primary bismuth minerals.|$|E
